<p>When you are done exploring your Developer Quick Start Trial, you can take the environment down just as easily.</p>
<simpletable>
<strow>
<stentry>
                    <b>Termination</b>
                    <p>
                        <xref
                            href="1.2devplatform.ALS-developer-trial-quick-start-troubleshooting.dita"
                            >Troubleshooting</xref>
                    </p><xref href="1.2devplatform.ALS-developer-trial-quick-start6.dita">Back to
                        Quick Start</xref></stentry>
<stentry><p>To ensure that all your resources are properly released, use the Horizon console.</p>
                    <b>Terminate the Instance</b>
                    <ol>
                        <li>Log into the <xref href="https://horizon.hpcloud.com/" scope="external"
                                format="html">Horizon console</xref>. </li>
                        <li>In the <b>Project</b> panel, select <b>Compute</b> and then select
                                <b>Instances</b>.</li>
                        <li>Click the checkbox next to the instance named
                                <varname>cluster1-core</varname>. </li>
                        <li>If you added a <tm tmtype="reg">Windows</tm> DEA node or a SQL Server
                            service, you will have additional instances to delete. The names will
                            all start with <varname>cluster1-</varname>. Check the checkboxes next
                            to those instances. </li>
                        <li>Click <b>Terminate Instances</b>. </li>
                    </ol>
                    <b>Terminate the Security Groups</b>
                    <ol>
                        <li>Log into the <xref href="https://horizon.hpcloud.com/" scope="external"
                                format="html">Horizon console</xref>. </li>
                        <li>In the <b>Project</b> panel, select <b>Compute</b> and then select
                                <b>Access &amp; Security</b>.</li>
                        <li>Click the checkbox next to the groups named
                                <varname>cluster1-SSH</varname>, <varname>cluster1-Router</varname>,
                            and <varname>cluster1-Internal</varname>. </li>
                        <li>Click <b>Delete Security Groups</b>. </li>
                    </ol></stentry>
</strow>
